page.text: With Highland Woodworking's Starter Woodworking Tool List, becoming a woodworker is easier than you
might think. This starter tool list includes a wide variety of tools used for general-purpose "straight-line"
woodworking--that is, tools and machines for turning are not represented. This is not intended to slight
woodturning, which is not only an integral part of much classic furnituremaking, but a fine sport unto itself.
The focus of this beginner woodworking tool list, however, is on the tools and machines most often used for
basic woodworking: cabinets, shelving, tables, boxes and other common projects. While this is a great
woodworking tool list for beginners, it is also helpful for more experienced woodworkers to prioritize tool
purchases. You can also browse our complete selection of
predilections, and there's doubtless plenty of room to debate the merits of any specific item. These are our favorites,
tools we've learned about, used and enjoyed during the past thirty years. Occasionally two or more similar tools are
, to offer a choice of features or price. You'll get what you pay for, but the less
expensive alternatives are nonetheless good, functional tools. Please consult the actual product listing for
specifications, additional options, related items and current prices.
The starter tool list begins with our favorite, traditional woodworking hand tools and highlights the variety of hands
tools available to build a great hand tool collection. We make recommendations on power tool options a woodworker
needs to cover the basic power tool needs of a woodworking shop. We also provide links to safety products which we
strongly suggest a woodworker use on a regular basis. Lastly, we have included key woodworking books covering the
range of skills a beginner needs to learn, good resources for even skilled woodworkers to have on hand.
Our catalog numbers are shown (where applicable) to help you identify the tools precisely. The tools are labeled to
indicate their usefulness in most shops and includes a range of tools from the "Must Have Woodworking Tools" to
